<h3>When to Use Claude</h3>
<p>Use Claude for <a href="/blog/seo-content-writing/">long-form SEO content</a>, content audits, competitor analysis with pasted data, schema generation, and any task that requires processing large amounts of text. Claude handles 8,000-word articles without losing coherence at the end.</p>
<h3>When to Use ChatGPT</h3>
<p>Use ChatGPT for quick keyword ideation with web browsing, short-form copy, meta description generation where keyword density matters, and tasks that benefit from real-time search data access.</p>
<h3>The Practical Answer</h3>
<p>Most SEO professionals use both. Claude for content creation and analysis. ChatGPT for research and quick tasks. The tools complement each other rather than compete.</p>
<h2>8 SEO Workflows With Claude (With Prompts)</h2>
<p>These are the 8 highest-impact SEO tasks you can run with Claude. Each includes a ready-to-use prompt template.</p>
<h3>1. SEO Content Briefs</h3>
<p>A content brief is structured SERP intelligence. Instead of guessing what to write, feed Claude the data from the top 10 results and let it build the brief.</p>
<p><strong>Prompt:</strong>
"I am writing an article targeting the keyword [keyword]. Here are the H2 headings from the top 5 ranking pages: [paste headings]. Here are the People Also Ask questions: [paste questions]. Create a content brief with: suggested title (under 60 characters), meta description (150 characters), H2/H3 outline, target word count, and 5 internal link opportunities."</p>
<p>This produces a brief that mirrors what ranks while identifying content gaps. Pair it with <a href="/blog/keyword-research-for-blog-posts/">keyword research</a> data for the best results.</p>
<h3>2. Long-Form Article Writing</h3>
<p>Claude produces <a href="/blog/how-to-write-seo-blog-posts/">SEO blog posts</a> that rank when you provide the right context. The key is not prompting "write a blog post." The key is providing a complete brief with data.</p>
<p><strong>Prompt:</strong>
"Write a 3,000-word article following this content brief: [paste brief]. Target keyword: [keyword]. Tone: practical, direct, no filler. Use short paragraphs (2-3 sentences max). Include a table comparing [X vs Y]. Add an FAQ section with 5 questions from these PAA results: [paste]. Do not use contractions. Do not use these words: use, strong, new, complete."</p>
<p>Always provide voice guidelines. Without them, Claude defaults to a generic AI tone that <a href="/blog/humanize-ai-content/">readers can detect</a>.</p>
<h3>3. Content Audits at Scale</h3>
<p>Claude excels at analyzing large amounts of content data. Export your page inventory with titles, URLs, word counts, and traffic data. Paste it into Claude.</p>
<p><strong>Prompt:</strong>
"Here is a CSV of 200 blog posts with columns: URL, Title, Word Count, Monthly Traffic, Last Updated. Identify: (1) thin content under 800 words with low traffic, (2) content decay candidates where traffic dropped over 50%, (3) consolidation opportunities where multiple pages target similar keywords, (4) pages that need updating based on the last-updated date. Output as a prioritized action list."</p>
<p>A <a href="/blog/how-to-content-audit/">content audit</a> that takes a team 2 days completes in 20 minutes with Claude.</p>
<h3>4. Schema Markup Generation</h3>
<p>Claude writes <a href="/blog/schema-markup-seo-guide/">schema markup</a> faster and more accurately than manual coding. Provide the page content and let Claude generate the JSON-LD.</p>
<p><strong>Prompt:</strong>
"Generate JSON-LD schema markup for this page: [paste page content or describe the page]. Include: Article schema with author, datePublished, and dateModified. FAQPage schema for the FAQ section. BreadcrumbList schema. Validate the output against schema.org specifications."</p>
<p>You can also use our <a href="/tools/schema-markup-generator/">schema markup generator</a> for quick implementations.</p>
